          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.The model calculated excitation function",
                "plays a transformation role for the data. We fitted the",
                "measured/model calculation ratio with a rational",
                "function, which described the deviation of the",
                "measured and calculated excitation function around",
                "20 MeV. For the fitting the 'TableCurve 2D' program",
                "of SPSS was used, taking into account in the weighting",
                "factor the uncertainties of the  measurement. First we",
                "used all available data. Then we removed those series",
                "of measurements which had many data out of  the 3 sigma",
                "limit. In the next step all other data were fitted",
                "and again some points outside the 3s limit were",
                "removed. In the third step we got the final fit",
                "function (see fig.4). Table 3 gives the evaluated",
                "cross sections with the 95% confidence limits as well",
                "as the calculated integral yields of 103Pd."
              ]
            }
